# Component Creation Guidelines

## Button Components
Always create buttons with these variants:

### Primary Button
```html
<a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Call to Action</a>
css.btn-primary {
  background: var(--primary);
  color: white;
  padding: 1rem 2rem;
  border-radius: 50px;
  font-weight: 600;
  box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.3);
}
Secondary Button
html<a href="#" class="btn btn-secondary">Learn More</a>
Ghost Button
html<a href="#" class="btn btn-ghost">View Details</a>
Card Components
html<article class="card [modifier-class]">
  <div class="card-header">
    <!-- Icon or image -->
  </div>
  <div class="card-body">
    <h3 class="card-title">Title</h3>
    <p class="card-description">Description</p>
  </div>
  <div class="card-footer">
    <!-- CTA or metadata -->
  </div>
</article>
Section Structure
html<section class="section section--[name]">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2 class="section-title">Section Title</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">Optional subtitle</p>
    </div>
    <div class="section-content">
      <!-- Content here -->
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
Grid Layouts

Use CSS Grid for 2D layouts
Use Flexbox for 1D layouts
Always make grids responsive
Use gap property for spacing

